org.conqat.lib.commons.collections

Class UnmodifiableList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.commons.collections.UnmodifiableCollection<E>
      • org.conqat.lib.commons.collections.UnmodifiableList<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>

    public class UnmodifiableList<E>
extends UnmodifiableCollection<E>
implements java.util.List<E>
    This is a wrapper for a List prohibiting all calls which would modify its contents. As the construction of this class is performed in constant time it is preferred over copying the list (which takes linear time). Using this class is also preferred to using the unmodifiableX() in class Collections as they return the collection base type that does not signal that the object is unmodifiable. Using the classes in this package makes unmodifiability more explicit.

    All prohibited methods throw an UnsupportedOperationException. The class is nearly the same as the one returned by Collections.unmodifiableList(List), but by making it a public class we can make the return value of some methods more explicit.

    This list is serializable if the wrapped list is serializable.

    Author:
    Benjamin Hummel
